    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Steal This Burger</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mary Elizabeth Brown letter comments on Arthur Lubow's April 19 article on rivalry between McDonald's and Burger King; says Burger King may want to promote itself as place where one can stay and eat family-style, noting Lubow's assertion that two-thirds of food sold by chain is consumed off-premises (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was interested to read that ''two-thirds of the food purchased at Burger King is consumed off-premises.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>I was interested to read that ''two-thirds of the food purchased at Burger King is consumed off-premises.''</p>
        <p>The food chain might want to consider promoting itself as a place where you can stay and eat. My two sisters take their young families to a restaurant where they can eat family-style, precisely because they don't want to mess up their own kitchens. So far, we're talking two mothers, five (soon to be six) children, and whoever happens to be going out with them. Multiplied by enough mothers who feel the same way, that might be the beginning of a nice customer base.</p>
        <p>Mary Elizabeth Brown  Staten Island</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
